glosses: to take away, remove, carry away, carry off, take out
to lead to a result or an end

examples.text: X kareler de birbirini götürdüğünde cevabımızı buluyoruz.
examples.translation: And when the x squareds cancel each other out, we find our solution.

etymology:
Inherited from Ottoman Turkish گوتورمك (götürmek, “to carry, take away”), ultimately from Proto-Turkic *köt- (“to rise, to raise; high, elevated”). Cognate with Azerbaijani götürmək (“to take, pick up”), Kazakh көтеру (köteru, “to lift, raise”), Kyrgyz көтөрүү (kötörüü, “to rise”), Turkmen götermek (“to lift, pick up”), Tuvan көдүрер (ködürer, “to pick, rise”) Uyghur كۆتەرمەك (kötermek, “to pick, raise”), Uzbek ko'tarmoq (“to raise, heighten”), and Yakut көт (köt, “to fly”). Related to göt (“ass, buttocks”).
Compare kaldırmak for a similar semantic change.
